# Documentation Updates

When you change code, architecture, conventions, or tooling, update the relevant documentation in the same task. Do not leave docs stale.

## Required docs to maintain

### Business logic (`docs/`)

Product behavior, domain rules, and app-level architecture decisions live in `docs/`. See [`.cursor/rules/business-logic-docs.mdc`](./business-logic-docs.mdc) for the full workflow.

| Path | Update when you change… |
| --- | --- |
| `docs/product/` | Vision, user roles, flows, feature scope, UX rules |
| `docs/domain/` | Entities, invariants, validation, calculations, workflows |
| `docs/architecture/` | Service boundaries, data ownership, integrations |
| `docs/decisions/` | Significant product or architecture choices (ADRs) |
| `docs/README.md` | Index links when adding new doc files |

### README files

| File | Update when you change… |
| --- | --- |
| `README.md` | Monorepo structure, stack, core principles, root scripts, getting started |
| `apps/api/README.md` | API layout, routes, handlers, schema, DB scripts, bindings, RPC entrypoints |
| `apps/frontend/README.md` | Frontend layout, routing, server functions, data-fetching patterns, dev commands |
| `apps/mobile/README.md` | Expo layout, routing, auth client, API client, dev commands |
| `packages/api-client/README.md` | Client usage, type inference, when to use HTTP vs service binding |
| `packages/components/README.md` | Subframe sync, component conventions, exports, Tailwind preset |

Update the README closest to the change. If a change affects multiple workspaces or cross-cutting principles, update the root `README.md` too.

